The paper deals with graph clustering problems, which are typically studied in the areas of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the problem, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The problem involves partitioning the vertices of a graph into clusters, which can be represented as geometric objects in some cases, making computational geometry (cs.CG) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses fixed-parameter tractability, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
